                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 20992/2–4.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Mexico</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">President of the United States</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-07-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 6, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Esteemed Mr. President</hi>: I have received your
                    courteous letter of the 25th of last month, in which you have been pleased to
                    very graciously and amicably invite me to meet you at El Paso or other station
                    of our frontier, during the trip which you propose to make in the Southwest of
                    your country in the months of September and October.</p>
                <p>I shall be most pleased to know personally the illustrious citizen who has
                    deserved the votes of his compatriots for first magistrate of the great nation,
                    neighbor, and friend of Mexico. I accept by this your courteous invitation,
                    provided that our meeting can be arranged for some days after the opening of the
                    Mexican Congress, which takes place on the 16th of September.</p>
                <p>With most cordial expressions of friendship, I remain, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Porfirio Diaz.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
